    {
      "@id": "beastiary:citation_isidore_2",
      "@type": "beast:Citation",
      "beast:extractedFrom": {
        "@id": "beastiary:source_etymologies"
      },
      "beast:hasPassageText": "The kid is so called from eating, for the young ones are very juicy and pleasing in flavor. Whence also eat and foodstuffs are named. Some people have said he-goats and she-goats are named from their cropping of bushes, others because they ‘hold to uneven places’. Some say it derives from the creaking of their legs, whence also they are often called crepae. They dwell in the high mountains, and even from a great distance they can still see anyone who is approaching.",
      "beast:isTextualReferenceOf": {
        "@id": "beastiary:int_goat_isidore"
      }
    },
    {
